In this tradition, sanyasis and sadhus go begging from door to door, receiving what the householder has offered and in exchange blessing them by chanting vedic mantras. Those who offer, whatever they may offer, have their karmas burned away by Paramashiva","message":"With the grace and blessings of SPH JGM HDH Bhagawan Sri Nithyananda Paramashivam, Kailasa Los Angeles Sangha began the spiritual process of Madhukari Bhiksha all over Southern California! Madhukari Bhiksha is an ancient Vedic tradition from India where ascetics went door-to-door to enrich families and give the opportunity for people to burn away karmas by accepting bhiksha (or donations). By receiving those who are Bhikshakas (going door to door) and listening to the message of enlightenment, you allow that very energy and auspiciousness to enter your space. Anything given by you to the Bhikshakas during their visit, be it a handful of rice, a coconut or a monetary donation, becomes a token representing your karma and relieves you of that karma! Swamiji has shared that “…whoever offers, whatever they offer, their karmas will be taken away.\" Just as a honey bee goes from flower to flower and takes honey from it without harming the flower, the person doing madhukari bhiksha will also go from place to place enriching and pollinating the world with enlightenment! To offer bhiksha and have your home blessed please fill out this form. A temple volunteer will be in touch with you to coordinate the bhiksha visit in the Southern California region. ----------------------------------------------- FAQs When will Madhukari Bhiksha take place? It starts on May 26th and will be an ongoing process with no definite end date as of now Can I offer bhiksha online? Bhiksha can only be done physically in person in the Southern California region. What does the bhiksha process involve? Devotees and sangha members will visit anyone who wishes to give bhiksha at your place of residence. We will stand outside your residence and observe protocols such as social distancing and wearing masks. What if I don't live in Southern California? How do I arrange to receive Bhikshakas and donate bhiksha? To offer bhiksha and have your home blessed please fill out this form and a temple volunteer will be in touch with you. What items can I give/donate as bhiksha? You can donate uncooked organic vegetarian food (lentils, rice, vegetables), money and other items. ------------------------------------ This Madhukari Bhiksha Process is just the beginning of a very special year for Kailasa LA! This year Swamiji has blessed for Kailasa LA to conduct Rath Yatra (traditional grand procession of deities) during the Chatur Masya (4 Month period) which starts with Guru Purnima in July until the end of Navaratri in November. Durin this Rath Yatra we will take temple deities on MANY grand processions around the Los Angeles. Please stay tuned for more information on the Rath Yatra and reach out if you want to be a part of the Rath Yatra! आई बाबा, तुमच्या मुलांना आता पंख फुटले आहेत, त्यांना खूप उंच भरारी घ्यायला , नेहमीप्रमाणेच तुम्ही मदत कराल, त्यांच्या पाठीशी उभे रहाल , ह्यात काहीच शंका नाही. तुमची चिमुकली, आता तेव्हढी चिमुकली राहिली नाहीत. तुमचे संस्कार, संगोपन ह्यांची शिदोरी घेऊन तीच चिमुकली आता एका वेगळ्या जगात पदार्पण करणार आहेत. आणि त्यांच्याबरोबर तुम्हीसुद्धा!! BUT BELIEVE ME, THEY WILL BE OK AND YOU WILL BE OK TOO!!! हे आहेत अनुभवाचे बोल!! ( हो, पण पहिले काही दिवस टिश्यू बॅाक्स जवळ ठेवायला लागायची शक्यता नाकारता येत नाही बरं का!) तर मुलांनो, आकाशी झेप घ्या, तुमची स्वप्नं साकार करा, आईवडिलांची शिकवण, त्यांचे संस्कार नेहमीच जवळ ठेवा कारण घ्या , खूप मोठे व्हा! तुम्हा सर्वांना आमच्या शुभेच्छा!! महाराष्ट्र मंडळ शिकागोच्या कमिटीतर्फे तुम्हा मुलांचं आणि आईवडिलांचं खूप अभिनंदन! आणि हा कार्यक्रम अतिशय उत्तम रीतीने पार पाडल्याबद्दल उल्का नगरकर, प्रसाद अथणीकर, प्रिया पाटणकर, अभिजीत रायरीकर, दीपा कामत, भारती वेलणकर, कश्मिरा मगर ह्या सर्व आयोजकांचंही अभिनंदन! आणि विशेष सहकार्याबद्दल मंदार जोगळेकर आणि वर्षा विसाळ ह्यांचे आभार! धन्यवाद, How can I avoid this? A: Why do you try to avoid it? To suppress pain, anger and humiliation will only cause it to stay in your system in a repressed form. Suppressed emotions can be dangerous - a little anger or hurt can fester over time into a deep and lasting hatred. Try accepting your emotions without judging yourself. Are you feeling hurt? Right. Now enter completely into the feeling of hurt. Don’t avoid it, don’t reject it. Don’t sympathize with yourself either, and don’t direct it against the person who hurt you - simply watch the emotion as it plays in your system. This may take a while - maybe a few hours, even a few days. And then you will see a transformation you never imagined. After all, emotion is energy, tremendous energy. Just how long can so much raw energy circulate in your system? The moment you accept your pain with no rejection, welcoming its role in your life, the whole quality of pain changes. The same energy that was pain, anger or suffering, is transformed into the blessed emotions of love and bliss. This is compassion, the silent force that moves in each of us, the force that transforms the ugly into the beautiful. And compassion brings its own reward. Just give yourself a chance and you can experience what I am saying! I don’t speak philosophy; I speak out of experience. I am answering some questions people have asked and I hope this helps everybody here. 1. I applied for NIE on May 23, 8:00 AM sharp. Mine was approved around 1:00-2:00 PM the same day. From my friends’ experience and mine, I see that NIE gets approved within a week or you may be asked additional documents to support it. 2. I am on H1-B, recently stamped in April and reasons I gave for NIE were - financial issues including rent and relocations, work related critical issues which cannot be handled with me sitting in the US, family issues due to which I originally intended to come to India and apparently now I am stuck. 3. I did not provide/ attach any supporting documents. Though in the email I did provide my Manager’s number and few others, whatever I seemed fit. 4. No special email/portal is required to submit this request. I applied via my personal email. 5. I applied to US Embassy New Delhi: NewDelhiNIE@state.gov. (That is where my Visa was stamped). 6. After mine was approved, I just had the NIE acceptance email on my phone, my negative Covid results and passport/tickets etc. for check in. 7. At check-in, they will ask for NIE acceptance or they also might call the CBP to confirm for the dates and all. But this shouldn’t be much of a worry. Make sure you are traveling within the NIE acceptance dates. 7. Everything was super super quick. Hardly 20-30 people on the plane. Traveling like business in economy, thank you. 8. When I reached there, they took me to the immigration area, to verify my H1-B. It surprisingly took me around 50 mins. But people who came after me were also called upon before me. I would say luck, eh ? 9. They just asked me question of what I do, how many years do I intend to stay, etc. Lower you mask, show them your good faces to verify and you are done. 10. And that’s it, get your check-in bag and voila ! Format for NIE : Last name : Your last name First name: Your first name Date of birth: Your date of Birth Place of birth: Your place of birth as in Passport Country of citizenship: Your country of citizenship Passport number: Your passport number Visa Number* and Category: Your visa number and category of the visa. Travel dates: Your planned dates. ( This is what is kept in mind while approving the dates). I said 1st week of June ) Travel Purpose : Work situation, Family situation and Financial situation. (Explain in details!) Give some supporting contact numbers, emails, etc. Thank You,
